# Collector fixtures are byte-for-byte captures of Linux tool output. A Windows
# checkout with core.autocrlf=true would rewrite them to CRLF, and `\r` is a line
# terminator in JS regex, so `.` does not match it: a CRLF row fails a pattern
# anchored with `$` outright rather than leaving a stray character. The parsers
# tolerate both endings, but the fixtures should still stay exactly as captured.
server/test/fixtures/** -text
